== Unit ==

The terms units and platoon seem to be used interchangeably. Presumably the element on patrol was a platoon, not a battalion (as the use of the term unit implies). If he returned to the "unit" there would have been more witnesses than just his platoon, as the reference to three other senior NCO's also suggests - a platoon does not have four senior NCO's. That suggests the involvement of more than just his platoon in the murder. The article does not make clear who was responsible and who was charged. And what about the officer in charge of his platoon? What was his role?[[User:Royalcourtier|Royalcourtier]] ([[User talk:Royalcourtier|talk]]) 07:04, 15 June 2016 (UTC)
